2026-06-09 | Can Place K People Without Adjacent Occupied Seats

	Question
Return true if all k people can be seated, otherwise false.
	Key Insight
To maximize the number of people seated:
		whenever a seat can safely be occupied,
		occupy it immediately.
This greedy choice never hurts future placements.
A seat i can be occupied if:
		seats[i] == 0
		and
		left neighbor is empty
		(or doesn't exist)
		and
		right neighbor is empty
		(or doesn't exist)
	Approach
1.	Traverse the seats array.
2.	For each empty seat:
		check left seat
		check right seat
3.	If both sides are empty:
		place a person there
		decrement k
4.	If k becomes 0:
		return true
5.	After traversal:
		return whether k == 0.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(1)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    bool canPlacePeople(vector<int>& seats, int k) {
        int n = seats.size();
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if(seats[i] == 1)
                continue;
            bool leftEmpty =
                (i == 0 || seats[i - 1] == 0);
            bool rightEmpty =
                (i == n - 1 || seats[i + 1] == 0);
            if(leftEmpty && rightEmpty) {
                seats[i] = 1;
                k--;
                if(k == 0)
                    return true;
            }
        }
        return k == 0;
    }
};
	Key Insight
Greedily placing a person whenever a seat is valid maximizes future seating opportunities. Since each seat is checked once, the solution runs in O(n) time and O(1) extra space.
